I'm sorry, but there is no package called ElevenLabs that I'm aware of for Text-to-Speech services in Node.js. However, you can use Google Text-to-Speech (TTS) API as an alternative. Here is a step-by-step guide to create an MP3 file using Google Text-to-Speech API with Node.js:

1. Install the required packages:

You will need the following npm packages:
- `@google-cloud/text-to-speech`: Google TTS API client
- `dotenv`: To manage your API key
- `fs`: To save the generated MP3 file

To install them, run the following command:

```bash
npm install --save @google-cloud/text-to-speech dotenv fs
```

2. Create a Google Cloud Platform account and set up a new project. Follow the instructions [here](https://cloud.google.com/text-to-speech/docs/quickstart-client-libraries) to enable the Text-to-Speech API and create an API key.

3. Create a `.env` file in your project and add the path to your Google Cloud API key:

```
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=path/to/your-api-key.json
```

4. Create a new file `app.js` and paste the following code:

```javascript
const textToSpeech = require('@google-cloud/text-to-speech');
const fs = require('fs');
const util = require('util');
require('dotenv').config();

async function textToMp3(text, outputFile) {
  try {
    const client = new textToSpeech.TextToSpeechClient();

    const request = {
      input: { text: text },
      voice: {
        languageCode: 'en-US',
        ssmlGender: 'NEUTRAL', // You can also use 'MALE' or 'FEMALE'
      },
      audioConfig: {
        audioEncoding: 'MP3'
      },
    };

    const [response] = await client.synthesizeSpeech(request);

    const writeFile = util.promisify(fs.writeFile);
    await writeFile(outputFile, response.audioContent, 'binary');
    console.log(`Audio content written to file: ${outputFile}`);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error:', error);
  }
}

const text = 'Hello, this is a test using Google Text to Speech API.';
const outputFile = 'output.mp3';

textToMp3(text, outputFile);
```

5. Replace `'Hello, this is a test...'` with your desired text.

6. Run the script:

```bash
node app.js
```

This will generate an MP3 file called `output.mp3` in your project folder containing the text-to-speech audio.

Please note that using the Google Text-to-Speech API might have associated costs. Check their pricing details [here](https://cloud.google.com/text-to-speech/pricing).

