To convert speech received as part of a WebRTC connection, you can use the Web Speech API SpeechRecognition object, which is designed for transcribing App Engine and AWS Lambda by converting speech to text. This approach is far from perfect and might not provide the accuracy or performance you desire.

If the conversation is simple text-based, I recommend using a third-party service like Google Cloud Speech-to-Text or Amazon Transcribe, which are designed to handle real-time streaming. These services are more robust and can provide better accuracy and performance

