First, ensure you have Rust installed. If not, you can download it here: https://www.rust-lang.org/tools/install

Next, let's create a new Rust project:

```sh
cargo new folder_watcher
cd folder_watcher
```

Add the "notify" and "tokio" crates as dependencies by editing folder_watcher/Cargo.toml:

```toml
[dependencies]
notify = "5.0.0-pre.2"
tokio = { version = "1", features = ["full"] }
```

Now, let's create the Rust program that can watch the Downloads folder, filter out events for a specific file name "target_file.txt" (or any other name), and automatically move the file when detected. Replace the content of folder_watcher/src/main.rs with the following:

```rust
use std::{
    path::{Path, PathBuf},
    sync::mpsc,
    time::Duration,
};

use notify::{watcher, RecursiveMode, Watcher};
use tokio::fs;

const TARGET_FILE_NAME: &str = "target_file.txt";
const DESTINATION_FOLDER: &str = "destination_folder";

#[tokio::main]
async fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error + 'static>> {
    let (tx, rx) = mpsc::channel();

    let download_folder = dirs::download_dir().unwrap();
    let mut watcher = watcher(tx, Duration::from_secs(2))?;

    watcher.watch(&download_folder, RecursiveMode::NonRecursive)?;

    loop {
        match rx.recv() {
            Ok(event) => {
                if let Ok(watched_event) = event {
                    if let Some(path) = watched_event.paths.get(0) {
                        handle_event(path).await?;
                    }
                }
            }
            Err(e) => eprintln!("Watch error: {:?}", e),
        }
    }
}

async fn handle_event(path: &Path) -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
    if path.file_name().unwrap().to_str().unwrap() == TARGET_FILE_NAME {
        let destination_folder = dirs::home_dir().unwrap().join(DESTINATION_FOLDER);
        if !destination_folder.exists() {
            fs::create_dir(&destination_folder).await?;
        }

        let destination_path = destination_folder.join(path.file_name().unwrap());
        fs::rename(path, destination_path).await?;

        println!("Moved the target file!");
    }

    Ok(())
}
```

Replace the `TARGET_FILE_NAME` constant with the specific file name you want to watch for, and `DESTINATION_FOLDER` with the target folder path where the file should be moved.

Now, build and run the program:

```sh
cargo run
```

This Rust program will watch the downloads folder and move the detected file to the destination folder. Be aware that this solution may not work on all platforms and may require elevated permissions to access certain directories. Please respect users' data and privacy when developing applications that interact with system directories.

